# SEO Restructure Plan for Equipment Listings

## Objective

Create a scalable, high-ranking SEO structure for equipment listing pages that:

* Eliminates QA/test noise
* Maximizes search relevance
* Supports dealer-based inventory
* Improves conversions

---

## 1. URL Structure Strategy

### Current Problem

Example:

```
/listing/qa-listing-prodealer-20260326/2021-tigercat-1075b-forwarder-qa
```

Issues:

* Contains QA/test strings
* Not user-friendly
* Weak keyword targeting
* Not stable for long-term indexing

---

### Recommended URL Structure

#### Primary (Canonical Listing URL)

```
/equipment/[year]-[make]-[model]-[machine-type]-[city]-[state]
```

Example:

```
/equipment/2021-tigercat-1075b-forwarder-atlanta-ga
```

---

### Dealer Integration (Optional but Recommended)

#### Option A (Subdirectory)

```
/dealers/[dealer-name]/equipment/[year]-[make]-[model]-[machine-type]-[city]-[state]
```

Example:

```
/dealers/kleis-equipment/equipment/2021-tigercat-1075b-forwarder-atlanta-ga
```

#### Option B (Query-based, not indexed)

* Keep dealer association internal
* Do NOT include dealer name in canonical URL

---

### Rules

* Lowercase only
* Hyphen-separated
* No timestamps
* No QA/test labels
* No duplicate words
* Keep under ~75 characters if possible

---

## 2. Title Tag Template

### Format

```
[Year] [Make] [Model] [Machine Type] for Sale in [City], [State] | Timber Equip
```

### Example

```
2021 Tigercat 1075B Forwarder for Sale in Atlanta, GA | Timber Equip
```

---

## 3. Meta Description Template

### Format

```
Used [Year] [Make] [Model] [Machine Type] for sale in [City], [State] with [Hours] hours. View specs, photos, and request pricing.
```

### Example

```
Used 2021 Tigercat 1075B forwarder for sale in Atlanta, Georgia with 3,150 hours. View specs, photos, and request pricing from Timber Equip.
```

---

## 4. H1 + Page Structure

### H1

```
[Year] [Make] [Model] [Machine Type]
```

---

### Page Sections (Required)

#### 1. Overview

* 150–300 words
* Include:

  * Machine type
  * Year
  * Hours
  * Location
  * Use case

#### 2. Technical Specifications

* Structured table (already implemented well)

#### 3. Condition & Features

* Bullet points

#### 4. Call to Action

* Request quote
* Call button

#### 5. Related Equipment

* Internal linking

---

## 5. Content Template (Reusable)

### Paragraph 1

```
This [Year] [Make] [Model] [Machine Type] is available in [City], [State] with [Hours] hours. Designed for [use case], this machine is ideal for [application].
```

### Paragraph 2

```
The [Model] features [key specs] including [horsepower], [reach], and [capabilities]. Built for durability and performance, it is well suited for demanding logging operations.
```

### Paragraph 3

```
This unit has been [condition statement] and is ready for immediate work. Contact us for pricing, financing options, and transportation details.
```

Can we implement AI to create descriptions of each product with the year, hours, where its at, undercarriage condition, tire size, etc? Or is that too complex?

