## 6. Internal Linking Strategy

### Replace Keyword Blocks With:

Contextual links inside content:

* "Browse more Tigercat forwarders"
* "View logging equipment for sale in Georgia"
* "See all used forestry equipment"

---

## 7. Schema Markup (Required)

### Types

* Product
* Offer
* BreadcrumbList

### Fields

* name
* brand
* model
* category
* condition
* location
* sku (stock ID)
* description
* image
* availability

---

## 8. Indexing Rules

### NOINDEX

* QA listings
* Draft listings
* Dealer preview pages

### INDEX

* Live inventory pages only

### Canonical

* All variants → canonical listing URL

---

## 9. Image SEO

### Requirements

* Descriptive filenames
* Alt text:

```
[Year] [Make] [Model] [Machine Type] for sale in [City], [State]
```

---

## 10. Site Architecture

### Category Pages

```
/forwarders/
/forwarders/tigercat/
/logging-equipment/georgia/
/used-logging-equipment/
```

### Purpose

* Build authority
* Capture broader search terms
* Support internal linking

---

## 11. Lifecycle Handling

### Active Listings

* Indexed

### Sold Listings

Option A: Keep page + mark as sold
Option B: Redirect to category page

### Expired / QA

* Remove or noindex

---

## 12. Implementation Phases

### Phase 1 (Critical Fixes)

* Clean URL structure
* Fix title tags
* Remove QA indexing

### Phase 2 (Content)

* Add overview content
* Replace keyword blocks
* Improve internal linking

### Phase 3 (Scaling SEO)

* Category pages
* Schema implementation
* Sitemap optimization

---

## Bottom Line

Your current system is structurally close, but:

* URLs are polluted
* Titles are not dynamic
* Content is too thin

Fix those three and rankings will move fast.
